### 5. `src/lib/oauth.ts` — `fetchWithConnectionError()` (line 84)

Inject custom headers before the `fetch()` call. Covers all 3 OAuth endpoints (device code, poll, refresh) — fixes the exact error from the issue:

```typescript
async function fetchWithConnectionError(url: string, init: RequestInit): Promise<Response> {
  const customHeaders = getCustomHeaders();
  if (customHeaders.length > 0) {
    const merged = new Headers(init.headers);
    for (const [name, value] of customHeaders) {
      merged.set(name, value);
    }
    init = { ...init, headers: merged };
  }
  try { return await fetch(url, init); }
  catch (error) { /* unchanged */ }
}
```

